    <h2 id="why-iron">Why Iron Gummies Are Replacing Iron Tablets in 2026</h2>

    <p>Iron is a fundamental mineral that your body requires for hemoglobin production — the protein in red blood cells that transports oxygen from your lungs to every tissue, organ, and cell. Without sufficient iron, oxygen delivery falters, producing the characteristic fatigue, brain fog, cold extremities, and exercise intolerance that affect an estimated 10 million Americans with iron deficiency and approximately 5 million with iron deficiency anemia.</p>

