    </div>

    <p>The shift from iron tablets to iron gummies is driven by a single pharmacological innovation: chelated iron. Ferrous bisglycinate — the form used in most iron gummies — bonds elemental iron to the amino acid glycine, creating a molecule that passes through the stomach intact and absorbs through amino acid pathways in the small intestine. This bypasses the free iron reactivity that causes GI distress with ferrous sulfate tablets.</p>

