        <strong>Energy Production</strong>
        <p>Iron is a cofactor in mitochondrial electron transport chain complexes I, II, and III. Without adequate iron, ATP synthesis decreases at the cellular level, producing fatigue that no amount of caffeine or sleep can resolve.</p>
      </div>
